post_text:
Bowling Green Schools is pursuing a state grant to assist students who have no Internet access with hotspots. Parents, if your student does not have access to the Internet to join our online classes, please complete the survey at this link no later than Tuesday so we have accurate numbers for our grant: https://forms.gle/J1WzgfQKwhRwJfhh6. Parents who cannot complete the survey should call their school offices on Monday or Tuesday.

The hotspots will only work on BGCS Chromebooks, and students must be enrolled in Click to Brick or Bobcat Virtual Academy courses to be eligible. All parents will be receiving a call and email Monday morning with this information as well.

BG Schools is also providing every student with a Chromebook. Parents should bring the signed Chromebook agreement or the Opt-Out form to their respective schools the week of August 31. More information about BGCS technology is available at: http://www.bgcs.k12.oh.us/content/technology

This facebook feed will not be responding to questions. Please direct questions to your school offices.

Bowling Green High School
February 23, 2019 at 2:41 AM ·

BIG congrats to our Bobcat swimmers!!!!

CJ Layne repeats as STATE CHAMPION in the 100 breaststroke! He set a new school record (54.48), new state record, tournament record, and automatic All-American! He also earned “Male Performance of the Meet” with his 100 breaststroke finals swim! CJ also placed 10th in the 200 free with a personal best time.

Jack Burroughs is the STATE RUNNER-UP in BOTH the 50 free and 100 free!

The 200 medley relay of CJ, Jack, Darrin Kirchner, and Zane Kirchner moves up to 9th place and earned All-Ohio honors while setting a new SCHOOL RECORD (1:38.66)!

Overall, these 4 boys placed 8th as a team! Gary Layne was also voted Division 2 Boys Coach of the Year! What a great state meet for our Bobcat swimmers! We are incredibly #BobcatProud of you!

Six of our BGHS band members were selected to perform in the Ohio Music Educators Association Honors Band! They were selected among students from six counties in northwest Ohio. They will be performing at the Stranahan Theater in Toledo on Sunday, February 17th. Congratulations to Sophia Bird (Tenor Saxophone), Culley Foos (Bassoon), , Allan Landgraf (Alto Saxophone), Simon Metzger (Percussion), Kate Tretter (Trumpet), and Sasha Zengel (Clarinet)! In addition, Sophia Bird and Simon Metzger were selected as first chair for their sections! Congratulations to each of you! #BobcatProud

shared_text:
Bowling Green High School
March 15, 2018 at 1:03 PM ·

Update: Jack swam a personal best in the 50m fly by 0.63 seconds and finished 153rd out of 312! Jack also finished 127th out of 200 in the 100m free. CJ ranked 21st out of 204 in prelims of the 50m breaststroke, and then swam a personal best by 1.6 seconds to place 19th overall! CJ also dropped 0.57 seconds in the 200m breaststroke to qualify 31st out of 161 for finals, and then dropped another 0.77 seconds to place 28th! No better time to swim your best!

BGHS swimmers Jack Burroughs and CJ Layne are currently competing at the NCSA Jr. Nationals in Orlando! Yesterday Jack swam the 200m fly and was seeded 167th. He finished 121st after dropping 1.08 seconds! CJ swam the 100m breaststroke prelims and tied for 16th out of 205. In the finals, he finished in 19th place after swimming his 2nd fastest time ever of 56.47! Congrats, Bobcats!

post_text:
At tonight's Board of Education meeting, the Board...

1) hired Cathy Schuller for the Treasurer's position that will be vacated by the retirement of Rhonda Melchi.
2) recognized Darlene Hecht, food service worker, for her quick action to save a choking student.
3) recognized student athletes Gracyn Amos (volleyball), Zach Applegate (cross country), Macy Hanus and Alli Fahy (golf), and Nick Jackson (football) for their league, district and state honors.
4) recognize OSBA Media Honor Roll: Marie Thomas, Clint Corpe, Larry Weiss, Jan Larsen McLaughlin, and Allie Hausfield.
5) listened to Jim & Dee Szalejko (BG bus driver & teacher) discuss the Dear Santa program that has supported 100s of BG families over the past 10 years. Look for opportunities to help soon!
#BobcatProud

1) hired Cathy Schuller for the Treasurer's position that will be vacated by the retirement of Rhonda Melchi.
2) recognized Darlene Hecht, food service worker, for her quick action to save a choking student.
3) recognized student athletes Gracyn Amos (volleyball), Zach Applegate (cross country), Macy Hanus and Alli Fahy (golf), and Nick Jackson (football) for their league, district and state honors.
4) recognize OSBA Media Honor Roll: Marie Thomas, Clint Corpe, Larry Weiss, Jan Larsen McLaughlin, and Allie Hausfield.
5) listened to Jim & Dee Szalejko (BG bus driver & teacher) discuss the Dear Santa program that has supported 100s of BG families over the past 10 years. Look for opportunities to help soon!
#BobcatProud
